# Backend API

This repository contains the backend server for the learning platform project. It provides REST API endpoints for authentication, courses, lessons, progress tracking, notifications, analytics, and dashboard data.

## Tech stack

- Node.js
- Express
- MongoDB (Mongoose)

## Prerequisites

- Node.js (v16+ recommended)
- npm (or yarn)
- MongoDB instance (local or cloud)

## Environment

Create a `.env` file at the project root with at minimum the following variables:

- `PORT` — port to run the server (default: 3000)
- `MONGODB_URI` — MongoDB connection string
- `JWT_SECRET` — secret used to sign JWTs

## Install

```bash
npm install
```

## Run

Start the server:

```bash
node server.js
```

For development with automatic reload (if you use `nodemon`):

```bash
npx nodemon server.js
```

## API Overview

Key route groups (see `routes/` folder):

- `POST /api/auth/...` — authentication (login, register, token)
- `GET/POST /api/courses/...` — course management
- `GET/POST /api/lessons/...` — lesson resources
- `GET/POST /api/progress/...` — student progress tracking
- `GET/POST /api/notifications/...` — notifications
- `GET /api/dashboard/...` — dashboard endpoints
- `GET /api/analytics/...` — analytics endpoints
- `GET /api/test/...` — test routes

See the route files under `routes/` for full details and parameter expectations.

## Project Structure

- `config/` — DB and configuration
- `controllers/` — request handlers
- `middleware/` — Express middleware (auth, validation)
- `models/` — Mongoose models
- `routes/` — Express routers
- `services/` — business logic / domain services
- `utils/` — helper utilities

## Notes for Developers

- Keep controller logic thin; put business rules in `services/`.
- Use the `middleware/authMiddleware.js` for protected routes.
- Add environment-specific config to `config/` or use `process.env`.

